q-calendar/disabled-after.description: A date in the form `YYYY-MM-DD` where all dates after, and including, will be disabled

q-calendar/locale.description: Used to change the locale of the calendar

q-calendar/max-days.description: The number of days to be displayed. Applicable only for custom-interval, scheduler and agenda views. Do not use with `week` or `month` views (set to 0 if setting the view dynamically)

q-calendar/short-weekday-label.description: Displays the weekday label in short format. For instance, 'Monday' would become 'Mon'

q-calendar/sticky.description: Turns on sticky resources and intervals

q-calendar/cell-width.description: Sets day cell width and turns on sticky mode. Width must be css measurement

q-calendar/transition-next.description: When animated property is true, transition to use for next calendar view

q-calendar-task/dark.description: Places the calendar into dark mode

q-calendar-task/no-aria.description: Turns off automatical generation of aria labels for timestamps

q-calendar-task/no-active-date.description: This controls whether the `q-active-date` css class is set when a user clicks on a date label (button)

q-calendar-task/short-weekday-label.description: Displays the weekday label in short format. For instance, 'Monday' would become 'Mon'

q-calendar-task/no-default-header-text.description: Do not display the weekday text in the header

q-calendar-task/no-default-header-btn.description: Do not display the date button in the header

q-calendar-task/min-weekday-label.description: The minimal number of weekday characters when truncation occurs

q-calendar-task/weekday-breakpoints.description: The breakpoint widths where weekday truncation occurs (needs 2 values)

q-calendar-task/locale.description: Used to change the locale of the calendar. Any acceptable locale can be used that is recognized by the browser. If the locale fails, then 'en-US' is the fallback

q-calendar-task/transition-prev.description: When animated property is true, transition to use for previous calendar display

q-calendar-task/transition-next.description: When animated property is true, transition to use for next calendar display

q-calendar-task/disabled-days.description: An array of string dates in the form `YYYY-MM-DD` that will be disabled. If an array is contained within the array with a start and end date, it will be treated as a range

q-calendar-task/disabled-before.description: A date in the form `YYYY-MM-DD` where all dates before, and including, will be disabled

q-calendar-task/disabled-after.description: A date in the form `YYYY-MM-DD` where all dates after, and including, will be disabled

q-calendar-task/disabled-weekdays.description: Similar to `weekdays` property, except values included in this array are automatically made disabled

q-calendar-task/drag-enter-func.description: The function to handle dragenter events

q-calendar-task/drag-over-func.description: The function to handle dragover events. You must call in your `e.preventDefault()` for Drag and Drop to work properly

q-calendar-task/drag-leave-func.description: The function to handle dragleave events

q-calendar-task/drop-func.description: The function to handle drop events

q-calendar-task/selected-dates.description: An array of string dates in the form `YYYY-MM-DD` that will be selected. Interval-based calendars use `YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm`

q-calendar-task/selected-start-end-dates.description: An array of two dates in format `YYYY-MM-DD` for selection purposes. Interval-based calendars use `YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm`

q-calendar-task/hoverable.description: Allows certain cells within the calendar to be hovered

q-calendar-task/focusable.description: Allows certain cells within the calendar to receive focus

q-calendar-task/weekday-style.description: Gets called to provide custom styling of a weekday

q-calendar-task/weekday-class.description: Gets called to provide custom styling (via classes) of a weekday

q-calendar-task/day-height.description: The maximum height in pixels for the day height. Using 0 will make the rows variable height based on content.

q-calendar-task/day-min-height.description: The minimum height to be used

q-calendar-task/max-days.description: The number of days to be displayed. Do not use with `week` or `month` views (set to 0 if setting the view dynamically)

q-calendar-task/cell-width.description: Sets day cell width and turns on sticky mode. Width is assumed to be in pixels
